C Library Functions:

***printf
***malloc
***free
***exit
***read
***write
***open
***close

***strerror
Prototype: char *strerror(int errnum);
Purpose: Returns a pointer to the textual representation of the current errno value (errnum).
Return Value: A pointer to the error message string.

***perror
Prototype: void perror(const char *s);
Purpose: Prints a description for the last error that occurred, optionally preceded by the string s.
Return Value: None.

***fork
Prototype: pid_t fork(void);
Purpose: Creates a new process by duplicating the calling process.
Return Value: In the parent, the process ID of the child; in the child, 0; on error, -1.

***wait
Prototype: pid_t wait(int *status);
Purpose: Waits for any child process to terminate and retrieves the exit status.
Return Value: The process ID of the terminated child or -1 on error.

***execve
Prototype: int execve(const char *pathname, char *const argv[], char *const envp[]);
Purpose: Executes a program specified by pathname with arguments argv and environment variables envp.
Return Value: Only returns on error, -1 is returned.

***signal
Prototype: void (*signal(int signum, void (*handler)(int)))(int);
Purpose: Sets a signal handler function for the specified signal signum.
Return Value: A pointer to the previous handler function or SIG_ERR on error.
Terminal-related Functions:

***readline
Prototype: char *readline(const char *prompt);
Purpose: Reads a line from the user with an optional prompt and adds it to the readline history.
Return Value: A pointer to the line read or NULL on EOF or error.

***rl_clear_history
Prototype: void rl_clear_history(void);
Purpose: Clears the history list used by the readline library.
Return Value: None.

***rl_on_new_line
Prototype: void rl_on_new_line(void);
Purpose: Indicates that the prompt has moved to a new line.
Return Value: None.

***rl_replace_line
Prototype: void rl_replace_line(const char *text, int clear_undo);
Purpose: Replaces the contents of the line buffer with the specified text.
Return Value: None.

***rl_redisplay
Prototype: void rl_redisplay(void);
Purpose: Redraws the current input line in the terminal.
Return Value: None.

***add_history
Prototype: void add_history(const char *line);
Purpose: Adds a line to the history list used by the readline library.
Return Value: None.